pros:
Staff are mostly friendly and civil; 
Good HR policy and lots of training opportunities; 
Reasonable salary; 
Very nice work environment with big and well-lit office space; 
Good location in central London.

cons:
Depending on which division you work in, sometimes you could be overwhelmed with workload, which then made it difficult to take annual leave or attend trainings; 
Change sometimes took very long to take place and this could be discouraging, because you wouldn't always get the support you needed; 
There was not a lot of room for promotion.
